			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>So, I've been noticing how many situations I've been put in in the last four years where students around me are easily connected and being productive in boring ass lectures and group activities and I, being Hella Poverty, am left out of the loop on assignments and information because I am not really high tech (pen and paper). <br />
<br />
I also notice I usually have a lot of ideas or corrections to code or other ideas I can make during school but these things get lost during the day, and making written notes of them is laborious and those also get swept way or ignored.<br />
<br />
At first I chocked all this up to me wanting a toy and simply not having the luxury of young-people toys, so I just ignored it and stuck to my Old Man Technology. <br />
<br />
Increasingly, though, I feel like I am seriously missing out on this and my productivity is being hurt, and it's time I got a tablet to take advantage of all the free wifi without lugging around a laptop or paying for expensive smartphone data plans. Powerful enough to get things done but not so much that it becomes a toy.  <br />
<br />
I would definitely use it, and it'd be a useful companion to my commuter life. Definitely more useful than my phone.<br />
<br />
So - I'm looking for something like a<a href="http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16834230930" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"> Google Nexus</a> - I need it to be able to word process (with a real keyboard, I would also need one of those) and connect to networks, being able to compile java or C would be great, too, and would keep me ahead of my own game and schedule.<br />
<br />
I'm trying to look up the current stuff myself but if anyone has ideas of what I should look out for, avoid, or consider if I decide to get one, please post up. <br />
<br />
Thanks!</div>

