			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>The last few years have been... interesting. They say that once you've hit rock bottom, there's only one way to go, and it seems my stars are aligned for another season. Tomorrow, I embark on a new journey, I'm not really sure if I'm ready for it, but I'm confident I can handle any curve balls thrown my way. I'm moving to New Jersey for a new job. I consider myself lucky that I can uproot myself like this, but I still feel a twinge of sorrow for the people I am leaving behind for a while. I don't know if I'll be back, but I feel like Seattle is and always will be my home, so perhaps some day my path will lead me back.<br />
<br />
To Mom, see you on Broadway in a few months<br />
To Matt and Krysten, you are the most hospitable people in the world, your generosity is renowned, and I will miss you all dearly<br />
To my friends, remember all the good times we've had together and I'll see you again<br />
To my coworkers, so long and thanks for all the fish<br />
<br />
To my new family, watch out!<br />
To my new friends, I will try to be more sociable<br />
To my new coworkers, I can't wait to see what's in store!<br />
<br />
This letter is not really going to be shared with anyone, but I felt like I needed to write it. It's been a busy week getting everything arranged, and there's still a ton of planning to do, but I needed to take a few minutes to reminisce on the last few years and take stock of where I've been and where I'm going. I've mended fences to a reasonable level with my ex, I've earned respect in the eyes of my coworkers and managers, and I've decided to move across the continent for a time. It just felt like I needed to say something about it. It's almost momentous.<br />
<br />
Thanks for reading.</div>

